    <!-- TTS浏览器信息相关字符串 -->
    <string name="tts_browser_info" tools:ignore="MissingTranslation">TTS Browser Info</string>
    <string name="tts_browser_info_title" tools:ignore="MissingTranslation">TTS Browser</string>
    <string name="tts_browser_info_content" tools:ignore="MissingTranslation"><![CDATA[
        <b>TTS Browser Overview</b><br/><br/>
        This TTS Browser displays all available TTS engines installed on your device, as well as languages and voices supported by the current default TTS engine.<br/><br/>

        <b>Features</b><br/>
        • <b>Engines Tab:</b> Browse all installed TTS engines with their icons, names, and package information<br/>
        • <b>Languages &amp; Voices Tab:</b> View languages and voices supported by the current default TTS engine, including details and search functionality<br/>
        • <b>Search:</b> Quickly find specific languages by language name or language tag<br/>
        • <b>Smart Sorting:</b> Default engines, languages, and voices are automatically marked and prioritized<br/><br/>

        <b>Quality Level Guide</b><br/>
        • <b>Very Low (100):</b> Understandable but unnatural, mechanical<br/>
        • <b>Low (200):</b> Not very human-like, but usable<br/>
        • <b>Normal (300):</b> Standard quality, sufficient for daily use<br/>
        • <b>High (400):</b> Close to human speech, more natural<br/>
        • <b>Very High (500):</b> Almost indistinguishable from human, highest quality<br/><br/>

        <b>Latency Level Guide</b><br/>
        • <b>Very Low (100):</b> &lt;20ms, suitable for real-time conversations, games<br/>
        • <b>Low (200):</b> ~20ms, suitable for interactive applications<br/>
        • <b>Normal (300):</b> ~50ms, suitable for general reading applications<br/>
        • <b>High (400):</b> ~200ms, network synthesis, quality priority<br/>
        • <b>Very High (500):</b> &gt;200ms, network synthesis, high quality<br/><br/>

        <b>Support Status Guide</b><br/>
        • <b>Available:</b> Fully supported language and region, ready to use<br/>
        • <b>Country Available:</b> Supports language and country, but not necessarily specific regions<br/>
        • <b>Variant Available:</b> Supports language, country and specific variants<br/>
        • <b>Missing Data:</b> Missing language data package, need to download in system TTS settings<br/>
        • <b>Not Supported:</b> TTS engine does not support this language<br/>
        • <b>Unknown:</b> Unable to determine support status
    ]]></string>

